.com/world/2023/aug/09/uk-could-leave-european-convention-on-human-rights-to-stop-channel-migrant-boats" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/mystery-totem-pole-appears-on-coastal-path-in-south-east-england" target="_blank">Mystery totem pole appears on coastal path in south-east England</a></h2><div class="description"> 8ft wooden pole erected on clifftops on North Downs Way in Kent, between Folkestone and Dover, has provoked interest for its inscription with the name Perkūnas, the Baltic god of thunder. Local speculation as to who was responsible for the pole ranged from art pranksters to aliens.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/mystery-totem-pole-appears-on-coastal-path-in-south-east-england" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/09/sutton-hoo-steamship-hulk-in-suffolk-gains-legal-protection-lady-alice-kenlis" target="_blank">Sutton Hoo steamship hulk in Suffolk gains legal protection</a></h2><div class="description"> The Lady Alice Kenlis was built in 19th century and is ‘important part of our national heritage’ It was designed by Hercules Linton, the Scottish shipwright who later designed the tea clipper Cutty Sark. The ship was abandoned in a river on Sutton Hoo estate and given legal protection.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 04:01:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><