nes</a></h2><div class="description"> London mayor and Met police commissioner say manufacturers must make phones less attractive to thieves. Attack where violence was used or threatened was carried out roughly every 55 minutes, amounting to 9,500 offences. London mayor Sadiq Khan and police chief Sir Mark Rowley say technology companies must design out the crime.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 05:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/nearly-two-fifths-of-robberies-in-london-last-year-were-for-mobile-phones" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/khan-tells-people-to-shun-nonsense-tiktok-craze-on-oxford-street" target="_blank">Khan tells people to shun ‘nonsense’ TikTok craze on Oxford Street</a></h2><div class="description"> Metropolitan police sending extra officers to central London street after speculation of ‘crime opportunities’ Sadiq Khan has encouraged people not to travel to Oxford Street to take part in a social media craze that he has described as ‘nonsense’ The Metropolitan police has said there will be a heightened police presence in the central London area.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:38:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/khan-tells-people-to-shun-nonsense-tiktok-craze-on-oxford-street" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2023/aug/09/italy-revises-bank-windfall-tax-uk-five-years-lost-economic-growth-mortgages-interest-rates-business-live" target="_blank">Bank shares rally as Italy waters down windfall tax; UK heads towards five years of lost economic growth – business live</a></h2><div class="description"> FTSE 100 index gains 56 points or 0.75% to 7583 points in morning trading. Italian banks are clawing back some of yesterday’s declines after the government watered down its windfall tax plans. Coca-Cola HBC is near the top of the UK after raising its revenue guidance.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 13:46:07 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2023/aug/09/italy-revises-bank-windfall-tax-uk-five-years-lost-economic-growth-mortgages-interest-rates-business-live" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/amazon-leaders-rich-countries-support-rainforest-deforestation-brazil" target="_blank">Amazon leaders fail to commit to end deforestation by 2030</a></h2><div class="description"> Eight South American presidents including Brazil’s Lula say rich countries need to pledge more resources to help protect rainforest. But they stopped short of committing to zero deforestation across the biome by 2030 amid divisions over oil extraction. The eight South American countries that are home to the Amazon rainforest said ensuring its survival could not be solely up to them.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:01:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/amazon-leaders-rich-countries-support-rainforest-deforestation-brazil" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/infighting-at-top-of-spain-far-right-vox-party-as-spokesperson-quits" target="_blank">Infighting at top of Spain’s far-right Vox party as spokesperson quits</a></h2><div class="description"> Iván Espinosa de los Monteros, a founding member, marginalised by hardliners close to party leader. He resigned on Tuesday saying he would not be taking up his seat in parliament. The far-right Vox party lost nearly half of the seats it won in 2019 elections.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 13:27:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/infighting-at-top-of-spain-far-right-vox-party-as-spokesperson-quits" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/france-missing-fire-holiday-home-disabled-people" target="_blank">France: 10 people die in fire at holiday home for disabled people</a></h2><div class="description"> One person still missing after blaze broke out at property in Haut-Rhin. Firefighters said they had discovered the bodies in the destroyed building. They had little hope of finding one other person alive after finding bodies in converted barn. Home for disabled people in north-east France was a holiday home for disabled.<