evacuations and closing schools in several communities. Coast guard rescues 12 people from the water off Lahaina, Maui county says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:50:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/hawaii-fires-maui-hurricane" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/china-warns-of-disease-outbreaks-in-flood-hit-areas-as-death-toll-rises" target="_blank">China warns of disease outbreaks in flood-hit areas as death toll rises</a></h2><div class="description"> Hebei province was struck by more than a year’s rainfall last week from storms that followed Typhoon Doksuri. Crop and animal diseases could break out as floodwaters retreated from rural areas in the north. Some cities struggled to restore drinking water supplies after worst flooding in six decades.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 04:51:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/china-warns-of-disease-outbreaks-in-flood-hit-areas-as-death-toll-rises" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/google-and-universal-music-working-on-licensing-voices-for-ai-generated-songs" target="_blank">Google and Universal Music working on licensing voices for AI-generated songs</a></h2><div class="description"> Google and Universal Music are negotiating a deal on how to license the voices and melodies of artists for AI-generated songs. Early stage talks are expected to include a potential tool fans could use to make AI-powered songs. The artists would have a choice to opt in to the process.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:30:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/google-and-universal-music-working-on-licensing-voices-for-ai-generated-songs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/09/wework-has-substantial-doubt-it-can-stay-in-business" target="_blank">WeWork has ‘substantial doubt’ it can stay in business</a></h2><div class="description"> US workspace-sharing firm once valued at $47bn made net loss of $397m between April and June. WeWork warned there is ‘substantial doubt’ over whether it will be able to remain in business. New York-based firm said its status as a going concern was in doubt.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:40:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/09/wework-has-substantial-doubt-it-can-stay-in-business" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/09/tui-hails-return-to-profit-but-warns-of-25m-hit-from-rhodes-wildfires" target="_blank">Tui hails return to profit but warns of €25m hit from Rhodes wildfires</a></h2><div class="description"> Tour operator reports first profitable April to June since before pandemic. But warns it expects to take €25m hit from last month's wildfires in Rhodes. Tui said wildfire bill will come out of full-year results, including cancelling holidays, compensating customers and covering welfare expenses.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 08:45:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/09/tui-hails-return-to-profit-but-warns-of-25m-hit-from-rhodes-wildfires" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/hell-in-a-ham-milkshake-i-tried-to-make-eight-dishes-from-the-bear-it-nearly-broke-me" target="_blank">Hell in a ham milkshake: I tried to make eight dishes from The Bear. It nearly broke me</a></h2><div class="description"> The Bear follows the lauded prodigy Carmen ‘Carmy’ Berzatto, an award-winning chef who returns to Chicago to take ownership of his late brother’s ailing sandwich shop. The FX on Hulu show was a surprise hit last year, each episode an elegantly constructed panic attack portraying the mania of Carmy's kitchen.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/hell-in-a-ham-milkshake-i-tried-to-make-eight-dishes-from-the-bear-it-nearly-broke-me" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/games/2023/aug/09/baldurs-gate-3-review-pc-mac-ps5-larian" target="_blank">Baldur’s Gate 3 review – awe-inspiring D&D rendition is a towering landmark</a></h2><div class="description"> Baldur’s Gate 3 takes place in Dungeons and Dragons’ Forgotten Realms setting. PC, Mac, PS5; Larian, uses the fifth edition D&D ruleset. A few homebrew tweaks aside, it's as faithful a rendition as you’ll find in the digital space.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 10:00:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/games/2023/aug/09/baldurs-gate-3-review-pc-mac-ps5-larian" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/andronicus-synecdoche-review-zoo-southside-edinburgh" target="_blank">Andronicus Synecdoche review – Shakespeare as gruesome gothic opera</a></h2><div class="description"> Polish company Song of the Goat strip Titus Andronicus back to tell a brutal tale of postwar violence, betrayal and revenge. The company, set up by Anna Zubrzycki and Grzegorz Bral, made its name on the Edinburgh fringe nearly 20 years ago with polyphonic pieces sung in an invented ur-language.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 13:51:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/andronicus-synecdoche-review-zoo-southside-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/09/jadie-david-the-legendary-black-stuntwoman-on-30ft-falls-motorcycle-jumps-and-being-set-on-fire" target="_blank">Jadie David: the legendary Black stuntwoman on 30ft falls, motorcycle jumps and being set on fire</a></h2><div class="description"> Jadie David doubled for Pam Grier on Foxy Brown and dodged moving cars in The Blues Brothers. She once spent an entire year in a body cast. David says she didn't pay much attention to an African American man who flirted with her in Griffith Park.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 09:00:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/09/jadie-david-the-legendary-black-stuntwoman-on-30ft-falls-motorcycle-jumps-and-being-set-on-fire" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/fiasco-podcast-leon-neyfakh-1984-subway-shooting-new-york" target="_blank">‘A shock to the system’: looking back on the 1984 New York subway shooting</a></h2><div class="description"> New season of Leon Neyfakh's Fiasco podcast relives a bleak chapter of US history when a white man became a folk hero after shooting four black youths. In May, military veteran Daniel Penny put fellow train rider Jordan Neely in a fatal chokehold, he claimed that he had acted in defence of himself and other passengers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:17:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/fiasco-podcast-leon-neyfakh-1984-subway-shooting-new-york" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/09/nicola-sturgeon-deeply-personal-revealing-autobiography-published-pan-macmillan" target="_blank">Nicola Sturgeon’s ‘deeply personal and revealing’ autobiography to be published in 2025</a></h2><div class="description"> Pan Macmillan will publish the former first minister’s as-yet-untitled memoir in 2025. Sturgeon resigned as Scotland's first minister in February. Nine publishers bid for the memoir at auction. Sturgeon said she would “almost certainly’ve written an autobiography, “even if it's just for therapy, for myself”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 10:49:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/09/nicola-sturgeon-deeply-personal-revealing-autobiography-published-pan-macmillan" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">From Pig Beach to Dunn’s River Falls: 10 must-visit Caribbean destinations – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is home to the world’s best beaches, pretty towns, waterfalls and national parks. There are stunning marine life, the best beaches and pretty towns in the world's most beautiful places. Here's the Caribbean in all its glory, including some pretty towns and waterfalls.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:35:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">From snorkelling to surfing: nine must-try Caribbean beach and water activities</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean offers a huge variety of tempting activities from snorkelling to scuba diving. Windsurfing and waterskiing is a must-try activity for everyone. The Exu Exu is one of the Caribbean’s most beautiful, vividly coloured coral reefs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:38:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Nightlife, loveseats and beautiful beaches: why the Caribbean makes for the perfect romantic holiday</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is an unbeatable destination for a romantic getaway with your loved one. From Jamaica to the hidden gem that is Curaçao, there’s something to suit every couple, whether on honeymoon, celebrating an anniversary, or just escaping everyday life for a taste of luxury.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:37:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Waterfalls, history and the world’s first underwater sculpture park: seven exciting things to do in the Caribbean</a></h2><div class="description"> The islands of the Caribbean are like nowhere else on Earth. From cocktails to coral reefs, they offer something for all tastes and tempos. Enjoy a classic mojito or piña colada on the white sand beaches of Barbados or Jamaica. Explore the area’s rich history and natural beauty.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:36:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/cross-border-kayaking-balkans-montenegro-albania" target="_blank">‘The police wave us off like old friends’: cross-border kayaking from Montenegro to Albania</a></h2><div class="description"> A six-day water-borne adventure takes paddlers through the Balkans to the Adriatic coast. Starting in Lake Skadar (Liqeni i Shkodrës), it spans both countries and is the largest lake on the Balkan peninsula. With a mix of wild camping, homestays and waterfront cabins, it’s the kesti.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 09:08:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/cross-border-kayaking-balkans-montenegro-albania" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/a-moment-that-changed-me-i-was-outraged-by-the-risks-facing-my-children-so-we-moved-to-the-country" target="_blank">A moment that changed me: I was outraged by the risks facing my children - so we moved to the country</a></h2><div class="description"> Black Caribbean people born in the UK have a higher chance of schizophrenia, and city life is a factor. So when a chance came to live in Somerset, I leapt at it. The life expectancy for any person diagnosed with a psychotic illness was 15 years shorter than the UK average.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 06:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/a-moment-that-changed-me-i-was-outraged-by-the-risks-facing-my-children-so-we-moved-to-the-country" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/how-to-make-the-perfect-vegan-moussaka-recipe-felicity-cloake" target="_blank">How to make the perfect vegan moussaka – recipe | Felicity Cloake's How to make the perfect ...</a></h2><div class="description"> Our in-house perfectionist scours Greece and the Levant for the best of the best vegan versions of this much-loved layer bake. Even in Greece, the 200-odd fasting days a year mandated by the Orthodox church mean that plant-based cuisine is more common than the casual visitor surviving on souvlaki and sea bass.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/how-to-make-the-perfect-vegan-moussaka-recipe-felicity-cloake" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/hmrc-froze-my-daughters-tax-free-childcare-account" target="_blank">After an HMRC error, my daughter’s childcare cash was frozen</a></h2><div class="description"> A payment of £779 into my daughter’s account was credited five times. Five months on, I still can’t get the cash to pay her nursery fees. More than 8,000 families were locked out of their accounts in February when deposits were erroneously multiplied by the banking provider used by NS&I.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 06:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/hmrc-froze-my-daughters-tax-free-childcare-account" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/you-will-be-missed-locals-seek-answers-about-destruction-of-crooked-house-pub" target="_blank">‘It’s gobsmacking’: locals demand answers to demolition of Crooked House pub</a></h2><div class="description"> 'Wonkiest pub in Britain' caught fire after being sold, before being demolished without South Staffordshire council consent. 260-year-old building is now a pile of bricks and timber after it was engulfed by flames on Saturday night. The former Crooked House pub in Himley, Staffordshire, caught fire and was demolished on Monday.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 18:45:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/you-will-be-missed-locals-seek-answers-about-destruction-of-crooked-house-pub" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/tiktok-how-shopping-went-social-hooked-new-generation" target="_blank">‘Where did I get my top? TikTok!’ How shopping went social – and hooked a new generation</a></h2><div class="description"> Zainab Hakim, 23, watches sellers livestream on TikTok, peddling their wares in real time. With a couple of clicks, she can buy things via the app via TikTok Live. Hakim bought eight items from eight sellers in just one afternoon.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:00:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/tiktok-how-shopping-went-social-hooked-new-generation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then, 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">UK students: do you plan to live at home during university?</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 90% of higher education students say they are worried about the rising cost of living. We want to speak to students who are considering living at home this year. Are you planning to commute in? Or are you going to live on campus? Are there other ways you plan on saving costs?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:33:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">UK workers: are you struggling to get the hours you’d like to work?</a></h2><div class="description"> We want to hear from ‘underemployed’ workers who are not getting as much work as they’d like. Whether you’ve had trouble finding full time work, have had shifts cancelled regularly or have had your hours reduced permanently by your employer since you signed up for the job.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:27:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/share-your-experience-of-travelling-outside-the-uk-for-ivf" target="_blank">Share your experience of travelling outside the UK for IVF</a></h2><div class="description"> People in the UK are increasingly funding IVF treatments privately, research shows. 63% of IVF funded privately in 2021 compared to 52% in 2019. IVF cycles funded by the NHS saw a decrease to 20,000 in 2021 from around 24,000. We want to hear from people who have travelled abroad for fertility treatments.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:05:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/share-your-experience-of-travelling-outside-the-uk-for-ivf" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Tell us: how have you been impacted by extreme weather in the UK?</a></h2><div class="description"> 2023 has been a year of deadly extreme weather, from wildfires in Greece, Algeria and Canada to heatwaves in India and Texas. We want to hear how people have been affected by heatwaves, storms and flooding in the UK in the last few years. The UK will face a greater frequency of flash floods, winter storms and summer heatwaves.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 09:25:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/09/premier-league-season-preview-arsenal-to-fulham-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Premier League season preview: Arsenal to Fulham – Football Weekly</a></h2><div class="description"> Max Rushden is joined by Barry Glendenning, Troy Townsend and Lars Sivertsen for the first of two Premier League preview shows. The Premier League season kicks off this weekend and in this, the panel run the rule over the top half of the table (as things stand, alphabetically)</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:25:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/09/premier-league-season-preview-arsenal-to-fulham-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/09/why-the-rest-of-the-world-cant-afford-to-ignore-the-coup-in-niger-podcast" target="_blank">Why the rest of the world can’t afford to ignore the coup in Niger – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The