ead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/law/2023/aug/09/leonard-leo-federalist-society-manipulates-free-speech" target="_blank">How Trump adviser manipulates free speech to advance his causes and ‘hurt his adversaries’</a></h2><div class="description"> Leonard Leo, architect of the rightwing takeover of the US judiciary, champions the first amendment for political gain but does an ‘about-face’ when it’s used against him, critics say. Leo, 58, is the low-profile, deceptively nondescript co-chair of the conservative legal group Federalist Society.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/law/2023/aug/09/leonard-leo-federalist-society-manipulates-free-speech" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/electoral-commission-and-psni-data-breaches-what-we-know-so-far" target="_blank">Electoral Commission and PSNI data breaches: what we know so far</a></h2><div class="description"> UK election watchdog and Northern Ireland police service both announce serious data breaches. UK data regulator, the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) is looking at the incidents. The incidents have raised immediate safety concerns over the consequences of leaking personal data. Here is what has happened and what we know so far.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 10:08:59 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </