n.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/09/saul-leiter-photos-paintings-in-pictures" target="_blank">‘There’s nothing quite like them’: Saul Leiter’s photos and paintings – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The iconic photographer considered himself a painter before anything else – and a new exhibition shows his colourful, abstract work alongside his photography. A new exhibition of his abstract work will also be held in London, London, at the end of November. The exhibition will run until December 31, 2015.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 06:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/09/saul-leiter-photos-paintings-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/08/the-women-calling-for-reform-of-venezuelas-severe-anti-abortion-laws-in-pictures" target="_blank">The women calling for reform of Venezuela’s severe anti-abortion laws – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> Century-old legislation in the South American country decrees up to six years in prison for those who have or provide abortions. Despite demands for change, the government shows no sign of reforming the 1926 law. Only in 2000 was it amended to allow for abortions to save the life of the pregnant woman.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.